# Metric Resource: FullCoverage
<https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/FullCoverage> a dqv:Metric, ftr:Test ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/FullCoverage" ;
    dcterms:title "Fraction of CQs whose required elements are fully generated"@en ;
    rdfs:label "FullCoverage: Fraction of CQs whose required elements are fully generated"^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:version "0.1.0"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
    dcat:landingPage <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/metric/FullCoverage> ;

    dcterms:description """
This metric aims to evaluate the completeness of CQ coverage by computing the fraction of CQs that are answered in full: FullCoverage = |{ i : cov_i = 1 }| / N. A CQ counts only when every required element appears in the generation and is correctly attributed to that CQ.

**Example:**

N = 4 CQs

Per-CQ coverage rates cov: [1.0, 0.5, 0.0, 0.7]

CQs with cov = 1: {1}    → count = 1

Result:

FullCoverage = 1 / 4 = 0.25

**What is being measured?**

This metric reports completeness, capturing whether each CQ is genuinely satisfied.
""" ;

    dcat:keyword "Ontology Engineering"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Metric"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Competency Questions"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Completeness"@en ;
    dcat:keyword "Coverage"@en ;

    dqv:inDimension <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/dimension/CQCoverage> ;
    dcterms:isPartOf <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/task/CQ2Term> ;
    dcterms:isPartOf <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/task/CQ2Onto> ;

    ftr:hasBenchmark <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/benchmark/ALL> ;
    ftr:supportedBy <https://w3id.org/cq4oe/> ;
    dpv:isApplicableFor <https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q184754> ;

    dcterms:creator <https://orcid.org/0009-0001-9475-8159> ;
    dcat:contactPoint <https://orcid.org/0009-0001-9475-8159> ;
    dcterms:publisher <https://oeg.fi.upm.es> ;
    dcterms:publisher <https://ror.org/03n6nwv02> ;
    dcterms:license <http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/> .

